glosses: To rise, to expand upward, to bloat, to inflate.
(for a liquid) To be about to overflow; to surge, to well up.
(for costs, a price) To increase, to rise.
(for an animal) To puff up, to fluff up to intimidate.
(for fabric) To pill up, to become fluffy or fuzzy.
To form blisters or bubbles on the surface due to moisture or heat.
(for emotions) To intensify, to grow stronger.
To puff up in a threatening manner.
To boast, to flatter oneself, to brag.

etymology: Inherited from Ottoman Turkish قبارمق (kabarmak, “to swell or puff up, to blister”), from Proto-Turkic *kāp- (“to swell, to form blisters”), possibly with the suffix Proto-Turkic *-gar. Can also be analyzed as kaba (“heavy, gross”) + -ar (“verb forming suffix”). Cognates with Azerbaijani qabarmaq, Kyrgyz кабаруу (kabaruu), Turkmen gabarmak.
